# Support Ticket Management System — Project Overview

Full-stack app for an AI capability exercise. Keep it small and clean — this is a Core-scoped project, not a production system. Do not add features beyond what's asked.

**Stack:** React (Vite) frontend · Node.js/Express backend · Postgres as a RDBMS · Jest + Supertest for backend tests.

**Structure:**
- `src/frontend/` — React app
- `src/backend/` — Express API
- `database/` — schema, seed data, setup notes

**Entities:** User (seed-only, no CRUD UI), Ticket, Comment. See `data-model.md` for exact fields.

**Conventions:**
- Validate all input on the backend; never trust the frontend alone.
- Every error returns a clear message and the correct HTTP status.
- No secrets in code — use `.env`, keep `.env.example` in sync.
- Prefer small, single-purpose functions over clever abstractions.
- Every new backend feature needs at least one test before it's considered done.

When unsure, ask before generating — don't guess silently on business rules, especially ticket status transitions (see `state-machine.mdc`).
